    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\n**Root cause:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.\n\n```typescript\n// Current (buggy)\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {\n\n// Fixed\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n```\n\nThe condition `i < items.length - 1` stops the loop one index too early — it exits before reaching the last element. Removing `- 1` fixes it.\n\n**Impact:** 4 out of 6 tests are currently failing (all `processItems` tests except the empty-array case). The `sum` tests are unaffected.\n\n**Change required:** One file, one line, removing ` - 1` from the loop condition. No test changes needed — the tests already assert the correct behavior.",
